## Experimenting with wealth redistribution

## The Hoover Index is the proportion of all income which would have to be
## redistributed to achieve a state of equity in the population. A Hoover
## Index of zero indicates a perfectly equal world in which no wealth has
## to redistributed. Contrast with the situation where all wealth in
## society is held by one individual: in this case almost all wealth would
## have to be redistributed.

## hypothetical income:
set.seed(42)
income=round(runif(10) * runif(10) * 1000)
avg_income = mean(income)

## Hoover Index:
H=0.5 * sum(abs(income - avg_income)) / sum(income)

## redistribution:
rel = (income - mean(income)) / sum(abs(income - mean(income))) * 2
income = income - sum(income) * H * rel


